statements: SELECT * FROM cash_flow_projections;
SELECT projection_id, projection_date FROM cash_flow_projections;
SELECT cash_inflow, cash_outflow FROM cash_flow_projections WHERE cash_inflow > 1000;
SELECT * FROM cash_flow_projections WHERE projection_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-03-31';
SELECT projection_id, cash_inflow, cash_outflow FROM cash_flow_projections WHERE cash_inflow > cash_outflow;
SELECT * FROM cash_flow_projections WHERE cash_inflow > 1000 ORDER BY projection_date ASC
SELECT projection_id, projection_date FROM cash_flow_projections WHERE cash_outflow < 500 ORDER BY cash_inflow DESC
SELECT * FROM cash_flow_projections WHERE cash_inflow > cash_outflow AND projection_date >= '2022-01-01'
SELECT AVG(cash_inflow) AS average_inflow, MAX(cash_outflow) AS max_outflow FROM cash_flow_projections
SELECT projection_id, SUM(cash_inflow) AS total_inflow, SUM(cash_outflow) AS total_outflow FROM cash_flow_projections GROUP BY projection_id HAVING total_inflow > total_outflow
SELECT * FROM cash_flow_projections

SELECT id, date, cash_in, cash_out FROM cash_flow_projections WHERE date >= '2022-01-01' ORDER BY date DESC, cash_in ASC LIMIT 10;
SELECT id, date, cash_in, cash_out FROM cash_flow_projections WHERE cash_in >= 1000 AND cash_out <= 500 AND date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';
SELECT id, date, cash_in, cash_out FROM cash_flow_projections WHERE cash_in > cash_out AND date < '2023-01-01' ORDER BY cash_in DESC, date ASC;
SELECT id, date, cash_in, cash_out FROM cash_flow_projections WHERE cash_in > 0 OR cash_out < 0 ORDER BY date ASC, cash_out DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT id, date, cash_in, cash_out FROM cash_flow_projections WHERE cash_in + cash_out > 2000 ORDER BY cash_in + cash_out DESC, date DESC;
SELECT * FROM CashFlowProjections ORDER BY projection_id DESC;
SELECT projection_date, projected_cash_in FROM CashFlowProjections WHERE projected_cash_in > 10000;

SELECT projection_id, projection_date, projected_cash_out FROM CashFlowProjections WHERE projection_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-06-30';
SELECT projection_id, projection_date, projected_cash_in, projected_cash_out FROM CashFlowProjections WHERE projected_cash_in > 1000 ORDER BY projection_date DESC LIMIT 10;
SELECT AVG(projected_cash_in) AS average_cash_in, AVG(projected_cash_out) AS average_cash_out FROM CashFlowProjections GROUP BY projection_date HAVING average_cash_in > 5000;

SELECT projection_id, projection_date, SUM(projected_cash_in) AS total_cash_in, SUM(projected_cash_out) AS total_cash_out FROM CashFlowProjections GROUP BY projection_date HAVING total_cash_out > total_cash_in;
